### ClickNBack — Workflow 2: User Registration and Offer Discovery
###
### Goal: Register as a new user, log in, and browse active cashback offers.
### Role: Anonymous → User
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - At least one active merchant with an active offer must exist.
###     Run 01-admin-platform-setup.http first, or rely on the demo data
###     that is pre-seeded in the live environment.
###
### Live API: https://clicknback.com
### Docs:     https://clicknback.com/docs

@baseUrl = https://clicknback.com


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Register a new user account
#
# Expected: 201 Created with the new user's id, email, role ("user"), and created_at.
#
# Business rules:
#   - Email must be unique in the system
#   - Password complexity: min 8 chars, at least one uppercase, one lowercase,
#     one digit, and one special character (!@#$%^&* etc.)
#   - The account is active immediately — no email verification required
#
# Note: The live environment is rate-limited to 5 registration requests/min per IP.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name registerUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice1234!"
}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2 — Log in with the new credentials
#
# Expected: 200 OK with an access_token and token_type: "bearer".
# Copy the access_token and set @userToken below.
#
# Note: The live environment is rate-limited to 5 login requests/min per IP.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name userLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice1234!"
}


###

# Set the token from step 2.
@userToken = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3 — Browse currently active offers
#
# Expected: 200 OK with a paginated list of offers that are:
#   - offer.active = true
#   - merchant.active = true
#   - today falls within [start_date, end_date]
#
# Each offer shows: id, merchant_name, cashback_type, cashback_value,
# monthly_cap, start_date, end_date.
#
# Use page / page_size to paginate through results.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/offers/active?page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — View the details of a specific offer
#
# Paste an offer id from the list above.
# Expected: 200 OK with the full offer object including cashback_type,
# cashback_value, monthly_cap_per_user, start_date, end_date, and status.
#
# Business rule: a user can only fetch details for active offers.
# Fetching an inactive offer returns 403 Forbidden.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@offerId = PASTE_OFFER_ID_FROM_STEP_3_HERE

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/offers/{{offerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
